<script lang="ts">
  const html: string = "<h1>Summary List Item</h1>\n\n<p>SummaryListItem is a single key-value row within a SummaryList. It renders a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrapper containing a <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> (term) and <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> (description) pair. The HTML specification permits <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> as a direct child of <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> for grouping <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> pairs, which enables per-row styling and attribute targeting.</p>\n\n<p>Use SummaryListItem inside a SummaryList to present structured key-value information such as order details, account settings, form review data, or any term-description pairs.</p>\n\n<h2>Implementation Notes</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Renders a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrapper containing a <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> element</li>\n<li>The <code>term</code> prop provides the key/label text in the <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> element</li>\n<li>The <code>children</code> slot provides the value/description content in the <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> element</li>\n<li>The <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrapper is valid inside <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> per the HTML spec for grouping dt/dd pairs</li>\n<li>The wrapper is transparent to assistive technology</li>\n<li>Spreads <code>restProps</code> onto the wrapper <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> for consumer customization</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Props</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>term</code>: string (required) -- the key/label text rendered in the <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> element</li>\n<li><code>children</code>: slot (required) -- the value/description content rendered in the <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> element</li>\n<li><code>...restProps</code>: unknown -- additional attributes spread onto the wrapper <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> element</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n\n<pre><code class=\"language-html\">&lt;SummaryList label=\"Order summary\"&gt;\n  &lt;SummaryListItem term=\"Product\"&gt;Widget&lt;/SummaryListItem&gt;\n  &lt;SummaryListItem term=\"Quantity\"&gt;3&lt;/SummaryListItem&gt;\n  &lt;SummaryListItem term=\"Total\"&gt;$29.97&lt;/SummaryListItem&gt;\n&lt;/SummaryList&gt;</code></pre>\n\n<h2>Keyboard Interactions</h2>\n\n<p>None -- this is a passive informational display, not an interactive element.</p>\n\n<h2>ARIA</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Semantic <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements provide description list semantics</li>\n<li>Screen readers announce term-description pairs naturally</li>\n<li>The <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrapper is transparent to assistive technology and does not interfere with list semantics</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Use inside a SummaryList to represent one key-value pair with proper description list semantics</li>\n<li>Use with an action link when users need to change their answer, including visually hidden context text for screen readers</li>\n<li>Use when each term-description pair needs individual styling or attribute targeting via the <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrapper</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>When Not to Use</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Do not use outside of a SummaryList <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> container -- it has no standalone meaning as the <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> elements require a description list parent</li>\n<li>Do not use for table rows -- use TableRow with TableTD instead</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Headless</h2>\n\n<p>This headless component renders a <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> wrapper containing a <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code> and <code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> element for a single key-value pair. It provides semantic description list item structure that is transparent to assistive technology. The consumer provides all visual styling for the wrapper, term, and description elements.</p>\n\n<h2>Styles</h2>\n\n<p>The consumer provides all CSS styling. The component renders with a <code>.summary-list-item</code> class for targeting. No default styles are included — this is a fully headless component.</p>\n\n<h2>Testing</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>Verify the component renders a <code>&lt;li&gt;</code> element with class <code>summary-list-item</code></li>\n<li>Verify pass-through attributes are applied</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Advice</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><strong>Designers</strong>: Keep term labels concise and consistent in width to maintain alignment across rows. Use visual weight (bold or color) to distinguish terms from descriptions.</li>\n<li><strong>Developers</strong>: Use the <code>term</code> prop for the key text and the <code>children</code> slot for the value content, which can include rich HTML. Use <code>restProps</code> on the wrapper <code>&lt;div&gt;</code> for per-row styling hooks.</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>Composition</h2>\n\n<p>SummaryListItem is designed to be used as a child of SummaryList. The SummaryList provides the outer <code>&lt;dl&gt;</code> container, and each SummaryListItem provides one <code>&lt;div&gt;</code>-wrapped <code>&lt;dt&gt;</code>/<code>&lt;dd&gt;</code> pair within it.</p>\n\n<h2>Related components</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li><code>summary-list</code> — an ordered list of key-value summary pairs</li>\n</ul>\n\n<h2>References</h2>\n\n<ul>\n<li>MDN dl element: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dl</li>\n<li>MDN dt element: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dt</li>\n<li>MDN dd element: https://developer.mozilla.org/en-US/docs/Web/HTML/Element/dd</li>\n<li>HTML spec div in dl: https://html.spec.whatwg.org/multipage/grouping-content.html#the-dl-element</li>\n</ul>";
  // BEGIN auto-generated component example consts
  const demoHtml: string = "<ol class=\"summary-list\"><li class=\"summary-list-item\"><dt>Name</dt><dd>John Doe</dd></li></ol>";
  const svelteSource: string = "// In your Svelte component:\nimport SummaryListItem from \"lily-design-system-svelte-headless/components/SummaryListItem/SummaryListItem.svelte\";\n\n<SummaryListItem>\n  <!-- SummaryListItem content -->\n</SummaryListItem>\n";
